---
layout: layouts/base.njk
order: 0
eleventyNavigation: Home
title: Swiss Sovereign AI, Productized
description: sysf.io builds custom fine-tuned AI models on Apertus — Switzerland's sovereign open LLM — and productizes them end-to-end with LangChain and LangGraph. Compliant by design, data-private, deployed in Swiss/EU jurisdiction or fully on-prem.
faq:
  - q: What is sysf.io?
    a: sysf.io is a Swiss sovereign-AI productization studio. We fine-tune Switzerland's open Apertus model on your data and ship it as a real product — orchestrated with LangChain and LangGraph, deployed in Swiss or EU jurisdiction, or fully on-premise. The result is a compliant, private, customized AI system you own — not a demo.
  - q: Why build on Apertus instead of OpenAI or Anthropic APIs?
    a: Apertus is Switzerland's fully open, multilingual LLM from EPFL, ETH Zurich and CSCS, with open weights and documented training data. Because the weights are open, we can fine-tune it on your data, run it entirely inside your jurisdiction, and give you full transparency for audits. With closed US APIs, your data leaves your control and you cannot inspect or own the model. For regulated Swiss and EU organizations, sovereignty and auditability are the difference between a pilot and production.
  - q: Does our data ever leave our environment?
    a: No. We can deploy inside your Swiss or EU cloud tenancy, on-premise, or in an air-gapped environment with confidential compute. Training and inference happen where your data already lives. There is no dependency on third-party US LLM APIs and no data egress by design.
  - q: How is this "compliant by design"?
    a: Compliance is built into the architecture rather than bolted on. Open weights give you transparency and auditability; in-jurisdiction deployment addresses the Swiss Federal Act on Data Protection (FADP/nFADP) and EU GDPR; and documented data lineage plus guardrails support EU AI Act obligations. We deliver the compliance and audit documentation alongside the model.
  - q: What does "end-to-end productization" mean?
    a: We take a use case from data preparation and fine-tuning through evaluation, guardrails, deployment, monitoring and ongoing iteration — with SLAs. You get a maintained production system with agent orchestration (LangGraph), retrieval (RAG) and tools wired to your systems, not a proof-of-concept that stalls.
  - q: How do we start?
    a: Most clients begin with a fixed-scope Pilot on a single high-value use case to prove value on their own data, then expand to a production Deploy and, where needed, a fully sovereign on-prem rollout. Book a call and we'll scope it with you.
